    <tr>
        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <p><b>Design Reference:-</b> <a href="https://tailux.piniastudio.com/" title="smart-link" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer">https://tailux.piniastudio.com/</a>  (you can provide dummy data for login)</p>

<p><b>Developer Requirement:-</b> Use required tailwind css icon, hero icon for development.</p>

<p><b>Story Requirement</b></p>

<p><span class="image-wrap" style=""><img src="/rest/api/3/attachment/content/10367" alt="image-20251029-144702.png" width="923" style="border: 0px solid black" /></span></p>

<ul>
	<li>Refer  to the screen shot. Top banner should show the loggedin user name with his designation and place.</li>
	<li>There should be “View Profile“ button in place of “View Schedule“.  Clicking on View Profile should navigate to Profile Page of the User.</li>
	<li>Replace “Appointment Request“ with “Jobs“ and Cards bellow the should look like this<br/>
<span class="image-wrap" style=""><img src="/rest/api/3/attachment/content/10368" alt="image-20251029-145101.png" width="795" style="border: 0px solid black" /></span><br/>
In Place of “Frameworks“, Company name should be there and in place of “What is Tailwind CSS?“ Job title should be there, I place of the image, company image should be there. after that make sure these data is present on card. Create a  model export class or interface and use dummy data.<br/>
<span class="image-wrap" style=""><img src="/rest/api/3/attachment/content/10369" alt="image-20251029-145338.png" width="708" style="border: 0px solid black" /></span></li>
</ul>


<ul>
	<li>After that in place of Users table, create a table name Jobs Applied. it should include column named Job Title, Company, Location, Date Applied, Status. Create model for this also and use dummy data for now.</li>
	<li>Add pagination. Per page 10 rows should be displayed.</li>
</ul>

            <br/>
        </td>
    </tr>
